from rnichol subject re truetype font that display but do not print in article avinash avinash chopde write i just instal a new truetype font under ms-window but though all the application display the font correctly on the screen quite a few of them fail to print out the document correctly on a laserjet non-postscript printer but when i use the window accessory write the printer print square box in place of the character of the new font yet write do display the font correctly on the screen thi be a common problem with highly complex truetype font microsoft admit to a problem with older version of the postscript printer driver but i find it to be pretty generic you can get around the problem by adjust the parameter outlinethreshold in the truetype section of thi entry specify the number of pels-per-em at which window will render truetype font a outline font instead of a bitmap font the default be i generally be able to get font to work by set depending on ymy printer resolution and the point size you be use you may need a different value the window resource kit warn against go above presumably that might cause font to print a square box or something i not smile bob nichol at t bell laboratory rnichol 